2. Tensors — multi-dimensional equations

Equations are scalar relations.

But tensors allow relationships across multiple dimensions.

Instead of:

x = y

you have structures like:

T_{ijk}

Each index represents a dimension of relationship.

Example:
	•	actor
	•	action
	•	object
	•	time
	•	location

The equation becomes:

Meaning(actor, action, object, time)

This is exactly the semantic tensor idea you were exploring earlier.

