3. Category theory — arrows instead of equals

Another alternative replaces equality with transformations.

Instead of:

A = B

we write:

A → B

meaning A transforms into B.

Then chains become:

A → B → C → D

And diagrams can represent entire networks of relationships simultaneously.

Example:

A → C
↑   ↓
B → D

This describes structure without needing equality at all.

